1
00:00:05,705 --> 00:00:11,823
Māyā is doing a necessary sevā

2
00:00:11,823 --> 00:00:15,773
to purify jīvas, to elevate them,

3
00:00:15,773 --> 00:00:18,331
to bring them into a higher position,
actually.

4
00:00:18,331 --> 00:00:20,408
That’s what this is all meant for.

5
00:00:20,582 --> 00:00:23,327
[By Fire Shall Hearts Be Proven]

6
00:00:23,327 --> 00:00:32,124
Well, that it’s a service,
The House of Correction.

7
00:00:32,124 --> 00:00:33,384
[Laughing]

8
00:00:33,384 --> 00:00:39,535
What’s the word?
Like judicial system, but …

9
00:00:39,535 --> 00:00:45,276
penitentiary … I mean,
these are English words.

10
00:00:45,276 --> 00:00:50,018
What is it called?
Criminal justice system …

11
00:00:50,018 --> 00:00:53,532
can’t think
of the precise word right now.

12
00:00:53,532 --> 00:00:59,227
It’s not meant really to punish …
oh, I know where I’m going …

13
00:00:59,227 --> 00:01:09,266
punish, as much as to rehabilitate.
That’s the word they use.

14
00:01:09,266 --> 00:01:12,985
Bhakti Vinod Ṭhākur
says just as

15
00:01:12,985 --> 00:01:20,330
to purify gold, you burn it,
put it in fire.

16
00:01:20,330 --> 00:01:26,199
I’ve seen this in Bengal,
going to the goldsmith.

17
00:01:26,199 --> 00:01:34,324
Just like Goldsmith
is a name in Europe,

18
00:01:34,324 --> 00:01:44,041
in India so often the gold shops would
have names like Lokki Narayan Babu.

19
00:01:44,401 --> 00:01:49,721
Lokki is the Bengali extrapolation
of Lakṣmī—

20
00:01:49,721 --> 00:01:55,485
from Lakṣmī, to Lakmi, 
to Lokki. Lokki.

21
00:01:55,485 --> 00:02:01,700
And still, girls refer to ladies
as Lakṣmī, Lokki. Lokki.

22
00:02:01,700 --> 00:02:03,949
So you give them the gold

23
00:02:03,949 --> 00:02:07,076
and they take out a lamp
and a flame,

24
00:02:07,076 --> 00:02:09,488
and they burn the gold.

25
00:02:09,488 --> 00:02:11,547
“Stop!!”

26
00:02:11,547 --> 00:02:14,222
They just immerse it in the flame,

27
00:02:14,222 --> 00:02:16,559
and the piece of gold you gave them

28
00:02:16,559 --> 00:02:20,683
becomes covered in black soot.

29
00:02:20,790 --> 00:02:25,475
It’s not looking very golden
at that point,

30
00:02:26,621 --> 00:02:31,144
it’s just covered 
in this black soot,

31
00:02:32,785 --> 00:02:40,214
but then you wipe it away
and there’s the pure gold.

32
00:02:40,783 --> 00:02:45,922
So, Bhakti Vinod Ṭhākur says,

33
00:02:45,922 --> 00:02:48,406
“If the suffering—
so-called suffering—

34
00:02:48,406 --> 00:02:55,352
inflicted upon the jivās—
the conditioned souls—by Māyā Devī

35
00:02:56,476 --> 00:03:03,466
is like that flame, and they’re
temporarily covered in soot

36
00:03:03,466 --> 00:03:08,643
but ultimately they achieve
the golden position

37
00:03:11,085 --> 00:03:15,058
—pure gold, pure cognition;

38
00:03:15,878 --> 00:03:21,131
jyotiḥ priti-tanum
hiraṇya-puruṣaṁ—

39
00:03:21,131 --> 00:03:25,568
then is it an objectionable thing?”

40
00:03:26,675 --> 00:03:34,641
So this suffering brings about
their liberation, ultimately.

41
00:03:41,213 --> 00:03:44,213
And as I’ve mentioned,
when I lived

42
00:03:44,213 --> 00:03:48,156
next to the fire chief’s residence
in San Francisco,

43
00:03:48,156 --> 00:03:53,799
there’s a plaque outside—you know,
brass shiny brass plaque—that said,

44
00:03:53,799 --> 00:04:00,880
BY FIRE SHALL HEARTS BE PROVEN,
LEST VIRTUE’S GOLD GROW DIM.

45
00:04:00,880 --> 00:04:07,958
So the case is being made there
that you need the fire.

